<% content_for :title, "How we score — AI Finder" %>

<section class="page-head">
  <p class="hero-eyebrow">Methodology</p>
  <h1 class="page-title">How we score</h1>
  <p class="page-sub">No sponsorships, no vibes. Every model is judged on the same rubric by a panel of rival flagship models, then the scores are weighted into a result.</p>
</section>

<div class="method-steps">
  <div class="method-step">
    <span class="method-num">1</span>
    <div>
      <h3>The same tests for everyone</h3>
      <p>Each model runs an identical set of tasks across <%= @categories.size %> categories — from writing and coding to privacy and enterprise.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="method-step">
    <span class="method-num">2</span>
    <div>
      <h3>Cross-judged, 1–10</h3>
      <p>Eight rival company flagships judge every answer against fixed band definitions (1–3 poor, 4–6 adequate, 7–8 strong, 9–10 excellent). A model never judges itself.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="method-step">
    <span class="method-num">3</span>
    <div>
      <h3>Weighted into a score</h3>
      <p>Each criterion has a weight. Criteria roll up into a category score; categories average into the overall. Higher-weighted criteria move the result more.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<h2 class="section-title">What a score means</h2>
<p class="page-sub">Every judge scores 1–10 against the same fixed bands, so an 8 means the same thing for every model.</p>
<div class="band-scale">
  <% Rubric::SCORE_BANDS.each_with_index do |band, i| %>
    <div class="band band-<%= i %>">
      <span class="band-range"><%= band[:range] %></span>
      <span class="band-label"><%= band[:label] %></span>
      <span class="band-blurb"><%= band[:blurb] %></span>
    </div>
  <% end %>
</div>

<h2 class="section-title">The rubric</h2>
<p class="page-sub">Every category, the weighted criteria behind it, and what each one measures. Higher weights move the score more.</p>

<div class="method-rubric">
  <% @categories.each do |name, config| %>
    <details class="method-cat">
      <summary class="method-cat-sum">
        <span class="method-cat-name"><%= name %></span>
        <span class="method-cat-count"><%= config[:fields].size %> criteria</span>
      </summary>
      <ul class="method-criteria">
        <% config[:fields].each do |field, weight| %>
          <li class="method-criterion">
            <div class="method-crit-text">
              <span class="method-crit-name"><%= Rubric::SUBCATEGORY_FIELDS.key(field) || field.to_s.humanize %></span>
              <% if (measure = Rubric::CRITERION_MEASURES[field]) %>
                <span class="method-crit-measure"><%= measure %></span>
              <% end %>
            </div>
            <span class="method-crit-weight"><%= (weight * 100).round %>%</span>
          </li>
        <% end %>
      </ul>
    </details>
  <% end %>
</div>

<p class="page-foot">Scores shown across the site are demo data until testing completes. <%= link_to "See the leaderboards →", leaderboards_path %></p>
